23 February 2022 GCIS hosts post SoNA media briefing of the Social Protection, Community and Human Development Cluster Following the delivery of the 2022 State of the Nation Address (SoNA), the Government Communication and Information System (GCIS) will, on Thursday 24 February 2022, host a media briefing of the Social Protection, Community and Human Development Cluster led by Ministers of Health, Dr Joe Phaahla and Basic Education, Angie Motshekga. The briefing will outline areas that President Ramaphosa mentioned in his speech related to departments in the cluster. Members of the media are invited to cover the briefing as follows: Date: Thursday, 24 February 2022Time: 13:00Venue: Ronnie Mamoepa Press Room, Tshedimosetso House, 1035 Francis Baard Street, Hatfield, Pretoria. NB: Live streaming details will be confirmed at a later stage. RSVP: Vanessa Mokaila on vanessa@gcis.gov.za Enquiries: Elijah Mhlanga, Head of Communication at the Department of Basic Education Cell: 083 5808 275